   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.1911_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>


               <address>
                  <addrLine>Springwood</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Kelso</addrLine>

               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1912-11-29">29. XI. 12</date>
               </dateline>

               <salute> My dear Hardy,</salute>

            </opener>

            <p>I was much grieved to read in the papers yesterday of the death of <persName
                  ref="#ps:EmmaHardy"> M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Hardy</persName>, &amp; I
               trust you will permit me as an old friend to offer you my most sincere symnpathy in
               your loss. I have very lively recollections of <persName ref="#ps:EmmaHardy"> M<hi
                     rend="superscript">rs</hi> Hardy</persName>'s unfailing kindness when I visited
               at <placeName ref="#pl:MaxGate">Max Gate</placeName> or called on you in <placeName
                  ref="#pl:London">London</placeName>, &amp; I shall always remember her with
               gratitude. I hope that your own health is fairly sustained, &amp; that I may see you
               when I am again in Town, tho' that nowadays is seldom &amp; only on the shortest
               visits.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>With renewed sincere sympathy &amp; kindest remembrance,</salute>

               <salute>yours ever truly</salute>
               <signed>G. Douglas</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.1911_2.jpg"/>


         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
